.SH BUGS
.SS Dash duplication
.PP
gocryptfs v2.1 switched to the \f[V]pflag\f[R] library for command-line
parsing to support flags and positional arguments in any order.
To stay compatible with single-dash long options like
\f[V]-extpass\f[R], an ugly hack was added: The command line is
preprocessed, and all single-dash options are converted to double-dash.
.PP
Unfortunately, this means that in
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
gocryptfs -extpass myapp -extpass -X
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
gocryptfs transforms the \f[V]-X\f[R] to \f[V]--X\f[R], and it will call
\f[V]myapp --X\f[R] as the extpass program.
.PP
Please use
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
gocryptfs -extpass myapp -extpass=-X
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
to work around this bug.
